wiki.summary: “CASE 143” is the lead-single and first track of Stray Kids’s eighth extended play MAXIDENT, released on October 7, 2022. The song was written entirely by Stray Kids’s production team 3RACHA, working on composition and arrangement alongside Korean producer duo 3SCAPE, and Raphael (Producing Lab.) (not much is known about Raphael, as this track is supposedly his producing debut). “143” is a numerically rendered shorthand expression, meaning “I LOVE YOU”, as the numbers represent the amount of letters in each word of the phrase. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “CASE 143” is the lead-single and first track of Stray Kids’s eighth extended play MAXIDENT, released on October 7, 2022. The song was written entirely by Stray Kids’s production team 3RACHA, working on composition and arrangement alongside Korean producer duo 3SCAPE, and Raphael (Producing Lab.) (not much is known about Raphael, as this track is supposedly his producing debut). “143” is a numerically rendered shorthand expression, meaning “I LOVE YOU”, as the numbers represent the amount of letters in each word of the phrase. “Stray Kids experiments with a new concept for this release, presenting our first love-themed title song for the first time. We tried to express love in a more Stray Kids-like way by comparing the confusion in the face of emotions felt for the first time towards [a] love interest, to 'an incident occurring' or analyzing love with the code '143 (I LOVE YOU)” — Stray Kids Read more on Last.fm.
